00:54:38.750 --> 00:54:40.590
OK, so the first
question on the Dory

00:54:40.590 --> 00:54:43.650
is what would you recommend
as effective methods

00:54:43.650 --> 00:54:47.130
for disciplining
children with autism?

00:54:47.130 --> 00:54:50.130
GINA BALDI: It depends
on the child, certainly.

00:54:50.130 --> 00:54:53.910
You want to teach and
get to those yes items

00:54:53.910 --> 00:54:55.780
as much as possible.

00:54:55.780 --> 00:54:59.970
And so certainly for some
kids, time out works--

00:54:59.970 --> 00:55:01.560
giving a break.

00:55:01.560 --> 00:55:05.650
But having them try again
is very, very important.

00:55:05.650 --> 00:55:10.560
So if it's a child
who pulls hair--

00:55:10.560 --> 00:55:13.650
I used to run a
center based program.

00:55:13.650 --> 00:55:15.581
And we had a little
boy who really wanted

00:55:15.581 --> 00:55:16.830
to play with these other kids.

00:55:16.830 --> 00:55:18.690
And he'd pull the
little girl's hair.

00:55:18.690 --> 00:55:21.230
And so teaching gentle hands.

00:55:21.230 --> 00:55:22.650
Oh, you can say, hi.

00:55:22.650 --> 00:55:23.490
You can pat.

00:55:23.490 --> 00:55:25.350
And so we were
right there to teach

00:55:25.350 --> 00:55:29.850
what he could do with his hands
to get that interaction that we

00:55:29.850 --> 00:55:31.890
knew he wanted.

00:55:31.890 --> 00:55:37.500
So what is the purpose
of that behavior and then

00:55:37.500 --> 00:55:39.450
looking for the replacements.

00:55:39.450 --> 00:55:41.100
What are the yes in those?

00:55:41.100 --> 00:55:43.140
Because the no is pulling hair.

00:55:43.140 --> 00:55:45.925
Explaining that to a child-- why
they can't pull hair and that

00:55:45.925 --> 00:55:48.300
the friend won't want to play
with them and all of this--

00:55:48.300 --> 00:55:53.310
for most kids, that's not going
to teach what should I do.

00:55:53.310 --> 00:55:56.440
And so teaching the what should
they do-- if you do a time out,

00:55:56.440 --> 00:55:58.840
you can say, OK, we're
going to take a break

00:55:58.840 --> 00:56:00.030
and then try again.

00:56:00.030 --> 00:56:03.570
Give them that opportunity
to try again if it's at home.

00:56:03.570 --> 00:56:08.820
But then help them be
successful as they try again.

