00:57:32.189 --> 00:57:33.730
AUDIENCE: Do you
have any suggestions

00:57:33.730 --> 00:57:36.790
if your child is
extremely food limiting,

00:57:36.790 --> 00:57:37.990
as far as their choices--

00:57:37.990 --> 00:57:40.510
as far as things to kind
of get them to open up

00:57:40.510 --> 00:57:43.630
to new foods and things?

00:57:43.630 --> 00:57:46.420
GINA BALDI: So that is
certainly a hard one

00:57:46.420 --> 00:57:50.560
because we get so scared of
our kids not eating that we

00:57:50.560 --> 00:57:52.780
many times will give over.

00:57:52.780 --> 00:57:55.440
I mean, and I know the
specialists out there

00:57:55.440 --> 00:58:00.520
that work with food issues
have long wait lists.

00:58:00.520 --> 00:58:01.900
But a lot of--

00:58:01.900 --> 00:58:04.150
and certainly,
you can call ESPA.

00:58:04.150 --> 00:58:07.600
And Christina can give
you some information

00:58:07.600 --> 00:58:10.450
and contact you
with other people.

00:58:10.450 --> 00:58:11.860
There would be no cost to it.

00:58:11.860 --> 00:58:14.930
We recently did a--

00:58:14.930 --> 00:58:18.640
for ESPA, I do parent
groups as well.

00:58:18.640 --> 00:58:21.550
If you ever want information on
that, they're free to attend.

00:58:21.550 --> 00:58:24.130
And you can do
remote and in person.

00:58:24.130 --> 00:58:25.330
And one was on food.

00:58:25.330 --> 00:58:27.845
And one of the tips that
this specialist gave,

00:58:27.845 --> 00:58:29.470
which I thought was
really interesting,

00:58:29.470 --> 00:58:33.500
is if your child,
say, is eating bread,

00:58:33.500 --> 00:58:36.850
well, you want to add just one
thing that complements bread

00:58:36.850 --> 00:58:39.160
that you think will be
acceptable like butter.

00:58:39.160 --> 00:58:42.550
You don't want to then say,
OK, here's spinach, right?

00:58:42.550 --> 00:58:45.250
Whatever they are
eating, you want

00:58:45.250 --> 00:58:47.980
something that actually
goes with that item

00:58:47.980 --> 00:58:51.610
to just get a different
taste on their palate--

00:58:51.610 --> 00:58:53.470
to just stretch them
with different texture,

00:58:53.470 --> 00:58:55.210
different flavor.

00:58:55.210 --> 00:58:58.930
That would be acceptable
for them to try.

00:58:58.930 --> 00:59:01.076
But if you--

00:59:01.076 --> 00:59:03.220
I don't know if my
email is on here.

00:59:03.220 --> 00:59:05.590
I can send you the presentation
this individual did.

00:59:05.590 --> 00:59:07.290
They had a lot of
nice tips in that too.

00:59:07.290 --> 00:59:09.410
I'll give you my
email as we leave.

00:59:14.622 --> 00:59:16.670
AUDIENCE: Do you have
any recommendations

00:59:16.670 --> 00:59:19.340
for when the kids
start to act silly,

00:59:19.340 --> 00:59:22.215
especially when they're not
comfortable with the situation?

00:59:22.215 --> 00:59:24.986
They start acting very silly--

00:59:24.986 --> 00:59:26.232
very, very silly.

00:59:26.232 --> 00:59:26.940
GINA BALDI: Yeah.

00:59:26.940 --> 00:59:30.830
And a lot of that is
some underlying anxiety--

00:59:30.830 --> 00:59:33.350
we see that as, or even
being overstimulated.

00:59:33.350 --> 00:59:36.350
So deep pressure
helps with that.

00:59:36.350 --> 00:59:39.320
I would put language to it.

00:59:39.320 --> 00:59:41.810
Start to help them discriminate
when that's appropriate

00:59:41.810 --> 00:59:43.490
and when it's not.

00:59:43.490 --> 00:59:45.600
If it doesn't feel
like a connection,

00:59:45.600 --> 00:59:48.740
it probably is
overstimulation, right?

00:59:48.740 --> 00:59:53.000
So depending on where you are,
sometimes holding some item

00:59:53.000 --> 00:59:56.476
that they can give pressure,
squeeze those balls

00:59:56.476 --> 00:59:56.975
or whatever.

00:59:59.880 --> 01:00:02.930
We used to put weight--

01:00:02.930 --> 01:00:05.030
the ankle weights-- you
open those up and put it

01:00:05.030 --> 01:00:05.900
on a child's lap.

01:00:05.900 --> 01:00:07.722
And that will ground
them a little bit.

01:00:07.722 --> 01:00:09.680
Their feet should always
be touching the ground

01:00:09.680 --> 01:00:10.744
to be grounded.

01:00:10.744 --> 01:00:12.160
If they're sitting
in a chair, you

01:00:12.160 --> 01:00:13.940
don't want their feet dangling.

01:00:13.940 --> 01:00:16.550
Because then they'd have no
way of grounding themselves.

01:00:16.550 --> 01:00:22.520
And they can kind of start
to get out of control.

01:00:22.520 --> 01:00:25.196
If it's somewhere
where you're sitting

01:00:25.196 --> 01:00:26.570
and you can put
them on their lap

01:00:26.570 --> 01:00:29.200
and give them some deep
pressure, that can help.

01:00:29.200 --> 01:00:32.930
Just that even weight
pressure on the shoulders

01:00:32.930 --> 01:00:35.900
to relax their body
and ground them.

01:00:35.900 --> 01:00:40.130
But you want to hold in kind
of a firm hold and with--

01:00:40.130 --> 01:00:43.890
not grab squeeze, because that
can work them up even higher.

01:00:43.890 --> 01:00:47.980
But just like squeeze and hold.

01:00:47.980 --> 01:00:48.997
I won't break contact.

01:00:48.997 --> 01:00:50.330
And I will do the rule of three.

01:00:50.330 --> 01:00:52.163
So if I'm giving a hug
or something, right--

01:00:52.163 --> 01:00:54.260
for a child-- then I'll say, ah.

01:00:54.260 --> 01:00:55.600
And there is my beginning.

01:00:55.600 --> 01:00:56.320
Hug.

01:00:56.320 --> 01:00:58.640
And I give this nice deep hug.

01:00:58.640 --> 01:00:59.910
And then I will let up.

01:00:59.910 --> 01:01:00.605
But I don't break contact.

01:01:00.605 --> 01:01:01.990
And I'll do it
the rule of three.

01:01:01.990 --> 01:01:04.640
Ah, hug.

01:01:04.640 --> 01:01:05.720
And I do it again.

01:01:05.720 --> 01:01:06.819
And then I'll open up.

01:01:06.819 --> 01:01:08.360
And some kids will
push back into me.

01:01:08.360 --> 01:01:10.120
I'll say, more hugs.

01:01:10.120 --> 01:01:13.630
And it's just to
relax their body

01:01:13.630 --> 01:01:15.690
so that then we can
have more focused work.

01:01:15.690 --> 01:01:18.560
And I can move on
to something else.

01:01:18.560 --> 01:01:21.830
Deep squeezes in the
hand really help.

01:01:21.830 --> 01:01:23.990
